==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lability
<hw>La*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Liability to lapse, err, or apostatize.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The property of changing readily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The property of being labile{3};
-- of chemical compounds; <as>as, the <ex>lability</ex> of some natural
products makes them difficult to isolate and identify</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Labimeter</ent>⟦br⟧
